#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:1
msgid "Building Python Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:4
msgid ""
"For complete build instructions see [here](../build_instructions/build.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:7
msgid ""
"VTK also supports creating a Python wheel containing its Python wrappers for "
"Python3. This is supported by setting the `VTK_WHEEL_BUILD` flag. This "
"changes the build directory structure around to match that expected by "
"wheels. Once configured, the build tree may be built as it would be normally "
"and then the generated `setup.py` file used to create the wheel. Note that "
"the `bdist_wheel` command requires that the `wheel` package is available "
"(`pip install wheel`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:14
msgid ""
"cmake -GNinja -DVTK_WHEEL_BUILD=ON -DVTK_WRAP_PYTHON=ON path/to/vtk/source\n"
"ninja\n"
"python3 setup.py bdist_wheel\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:20
msgid ""
"Any modules may be turned on or off as in a normal VTK build. Certain "
"modules add features to the generated wheel to indicate their availability. "
"These flags are not meant to be comprehensive, but any reasonable feature "
"flags may be added to `CMake/vtkWheelFinalization.cmake` as needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:25
msgid ""
"Note that the wheel will not include any external third party libraries in "
"its wheel (e.g., X11, OpenGL, etc.) to avoid conflicts with systems or other "
"wheels doing the same."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:29
msgid "Modifying Version and/or Distribution Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:31
msgid ""
"When generating a wheel, you can modify the distribution name and/or add a "
"suffix to the wheel version string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:34
msgid ""
"By default, the distribution name is `vtk` though you can add a suffix via "
"the `VTK_DIST_NAME_SUFFIX` CMake variable (e.g., set "
"`VTK_DIST_NAME_SUFFIX`). An underscore (`_`) character is automatically "
"placed between `vtk` and the value of `VTK_DIST_NAME_SUFFIX`. Please use `_` "
"characters for further delimination in the suffix value. Example setting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:40
msgid "set(VTK_DIST_NAME_SUFFIX \"foo\" CACHE STRING \"\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:44
msgid ""
"By default (outside of a CI release build), `dev0` is appended to the "
"version of the package (e.g., `9.2.2.dev0`). This suffix can be controlled "
"through the `VTK_VERSION_SUFFIX` CMake variable and is useful if generating "
"multiple wheels and wanting to differentiate the build variants by the "
"version string of the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:50
msgid "set(VTK_VERSION_SUFFIX \"dev0\" CACHE STRING \"\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:54
msgid "Generating the wheel SDK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:56
msgid ""
"This is an optional step that may be useful if you need to build python "
"extensions against the generated Python wheel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:58
msgid "Before building the vtk-sdk wheel, one must ensure that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:59
msgid ""
"`CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` is defined to a meaningful value, DO **NOT** use the "
"`--prefix` option of `cmake --install`!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:60
msgid ""
"*Optional*: `VTK_VERSION_SUFFIX` is set to some meaningful value, see above "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:61
msgid ""
"Install prefix is clean, all files in the install prefix will be packaged!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:62
msgid "VTK has been built with `VTK_WHEEL_BUILD=ON`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:63
msgid ""
"VTK has been installed, using `cmake --install` or by \"building\" the "
"install target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:65
msgid ""
"Then move to the `${CMAKE_BUILD_DIR}/wheel_sdks` directory and run the "
"following command:</br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:65
#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:70
msgid "</br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:66
msgid "python -m pip wheel .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_python_wheels.md:70
msgid ""
"A `vtk_sdk-<version>-<pyabi>-<platform-tag>.whl` wheel will be generated in "
"the `${CMAKE_BUILD_DIR}/wheel_sdks` folder.</br> Generated wheel is only "
"**guaranteed to be compatible with the VTK install tree and wheel that you "
"may have generated using the same build**. This is due to VTK not having any "
"ABI stability guarantees.</br> In practice, it is likely that it will be "
"compatible with any generated VTK with same optimization level and same "
"commit hash."
msgstr ""
